rlm-fe

Fuzzy-edit. Pick one or more files reachable from the current
directory (recursive) using fzf, then open them in $EDITOR. The file
contents are shown in the fzf preview pane. Press Tab to mark files
for multi-select, Enter to open, Ctrl-P to cycle the preview pane
height.

Files are listed with fd, including hidden and gitignored files (the
.git directory is excluded). The display column is relative to the
current directory; the full absolute path is what the picker acts on.

Entries are sorted by recently-selected first, then by file mtime
descending for entries that have never been picked. Within
previously-picked entries, the most-recent pick wins.

MRU history is recorded by the shared helper _rlm-fe-history in
~/.cache/rlm-fe/history.tsv, keyed on each file's full absolute path.
Because the cache stores full paths, a file keeps its MRU rank no
matter which directory rlm-fe is run from.

ENVIRONMENT
  EDITOR   Editor to open the selected files (falls back to vi).

REQUIRES
  fd, fzf, python3
